M|rules|title: Per-Request Deduplication with React.cache()
M|rules|impact: MEDIUM
M|rules|impactDescription: deduplicates within request
M|rules|tags: server, cache, react-cache, deduplication
M|rules|Use `React.cache()` for server-side request deduplication. Authentication and database queries benefit most.
M|rules|**Usage:**
M|rules|```typescript
M|rules|import { cache } from 'react'
M|rules|export const getCurrentUser = cache(async () => {
M|rules|const ses = await auth()
M|rules|if (!ses?.user?.id) return null
M|rules|return await db.user.findUnique({
M|rules|where: { id: ses.user.id }
M|rules|})
M|rules|})
M|rules|```
M|rules|Within a single request, multiple calls to `getCurrentUser()` execute the query only once.
M|rules|**Avoid inline objects as arguments:**
M|rules|`React.cache()` uses shallow equality (`Object.is`) to determine cache hits. Inline objects create new references each call, preventing cache hits.
M|rules|**Incorrect (always cache miss):**
M|rules|```typescript
M|rules|const getUser = cache(async (params: { uid: number }) => {
M|rules|return await db.user.findUnique({ where: { id: params.uid } })
M|rules|})
M|rules|// Each call creates new object, never hits cache
M|rules|getUser({ uid: 1 })
M|rules|getUser({ uid: 1 })  // Cache miss, runs query again
M|rules|```
M|rules|**Correct (cache hit):**
M|rules|```typescript
M|rules|const getUser = cache(async (uid: number) => {
M|rules|return await db.user.findUnique({ where: { id: uid } })
M|rules|})
M|rules|// Primitive args use value equality
M|rules|getUser(1)
M|rules|getUser(1)  // Cache hit, returns cached result
M|rules|```
M|rules|If you must pass objects, pass the same reference:
M|rules|```typescript
M|rules|const params = { uid: 1 }
M|rules|getUser(params)  // Query runs
M|rules|getUser(params)  // Cache hit (same reference)
M|rules|```
M|rules|**Next.js-Specific Note:**
M|rules|In Next.js, the `fetch` API is automatically extended with request memoization. Requests with the same URL and options are automatically deduplicated within a single request, so you don't need `React.
M|rules|- Database queries (Prisma, Drizzle, etc.)
M|rules|- Heavy computations
M|rules|- Authentication checks
M|rules|- File system operations
M|rules|- Any non-fetch async work
M|rules|Use `React.cache()` to deduplicate these operations across your component tree.
M|rules|Reference: [React.cache documentation](https://react.dev/reference/react/cache)